article.headline: SE Louisiana 73, Millsaps 55
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Kevyn Green scored 19 points and grabbed eight rebounds Sunday to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 73-55 win over Millsaps. Millsaps (3-1) never led as Southeastern (4-1) took a 40-35 halftime lead and quickly accelerated behind the shooting of Green, who had five 3-pointers, and Patrick Sullivan and Warrell Span, who had 12 points each. Sullivan added nine rebounds. Chad Songy was the only scorer for Millsaps in double figures with 15 points. Deonte Oscar and Rodney Rogan had 8 each. Southeastern sank five of seven 3-pointers in the second half, while Millsaps managed only 2 of 12. Southeastern also shot 93 percent from the free-throw line with 13-of-14, while Millsaps could only sink 60 percent.
